Dungeons and Dragons Icons Armory
Ver 1.0.0
Dec 18, 2018

For easy transfer to saved D&D games, I recommend saving either the Armory Spawner or the Armory Bag to your personal chest.

Thanks for subscribing to my mod, I hope you enjoy the tokens!

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Custom tokens used in various campaigns I've been a part of.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I wondered what it would be like to try to boop a kobold on its snout, but then I think a previous life reminded me that usually doesn't go well."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Melech found a flask that never seemed to run dry of water. It'll do in a pinch, but I would've preferred that he came across a never-empty flask of ale."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Skrit no like the first icon, must tell artist to draw him another one that doesn't make Skrit look silly."
-Skrit, Barbarian (and critic)

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I wouldn't call it particularly elegant to look at, but it's hard to argue with results."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I don't know where he got that frying pan from, but I have a feeling someone somewhere in the world is short one pan in their kitchen."
-Garlen Sunbourne, Paladin

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I didn't STEAL it from him, I took it off his person after DISARMING him. That's a key difference, I'll have you know."
-Garlen Sunbourne, Paladin

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"How poetic. I wanted to forsake the darkness, and yet here it offers me strength."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"The light of Pelor illuminates my path!"
-Garlen Sunbourne, Paladin

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Found amongst a pile of treasures, used by none since there was a better sword in the pile as well."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Gift from king! NO TAKE."
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Skrit sees light!... it's alright."
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"At first, I questioned the sanity of the monk as he waded into the fray of battle without even so much as a scrap of armor on him. However, I changed my mind when there was not a single scratch on him after the fight. He moved like the very breeze itself, dodging any attack that came his way.
Maybe he could only be pinned down if you offered him his favourite ale."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"You know, I don't think I ever discerned what this does, but I think the paladin was envious of it, so it gave me some satisfaction at the very least"
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Grabby grabby for the shinies, slashy slashy for the ones who take shinies!"
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"The ancient one of the lizardmen gave us these as thanks for freeing his followers from the parasitic creatures of the forest. Keeping it close to me makes me feel stronger. Either that or I got a good rest last night."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"A mystical set of beads that grant wishes. Anything I could ever want, yet I feel I already have enough.
Wonder if I could make a proverb out of that."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"SSSSSKRRRRRRRIIIIIIITTTTT!!!!!!"
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A book might contain poetry, historical accounts, information pertaining to a particular field of lore, diagrams and notes on gnomish contraptions, or just about anything else that can be represented using text or pictures. A book of spells is a spellbook.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A set of pulleys with a cable threaded through them and a hook to attach to objects, a block and tackle allows you to hoist up to four times the weight you can normally lift.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A thick, quilted, blanket made to keep you warm in cold weather.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
A backpack is a leather pack carried on the back, typically with straps to secure it. A backpack can hold 1 cubic foot/ 30 pounds of gear.
You can also strap items, such as a bedroll or a coil of rope, to the outside of a backpack.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A creature that drinks this vial of liquid gains advantage on saving throws against poison for 1 hour. It confers no benefit to undead or constructs.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can throw this flask up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. Make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the alchemist's fire as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 1d4 fire damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature can end this damage by using its action to make a DC 10 Dexterity check to extinguish the flames.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can splash the contents of this vial onto a creature within 5 feet of you or throw the vial up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the acid as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 2d6 acid damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes could consist of boots, a wool skirt or breeches, a sturdy belt, a shirt (perhaps with a vest or jacket), and an ample cloak with a hood.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard whetstone used to sharpen blades.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A waterskin can hold 4 pints of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A vial can hold 4 ounces of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A torch burns for 1 hour, providing bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. If you make a melee attack with a burning torch and hit, it deals 1 fire damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This small container holds flint, fire steel, and tinder (usually dry cloth soaked in light oil) used to kindle a fire. Using it to light a torch -- or anything else with abundant, exposed fuel -- takes an action. Lighting any other fire takes 1 minute.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A simple and portable canvas shelter, a tent sleeps two.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When you suspect a trap, you can put the end of your 10-foot pole through that hole in the wall instead of reaching in with your hand.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A steel mirror is handy when you want to look around corners, signal friends with reflected sunlight, keep an eye on a medusa, make sure that you look good enough to present yourself to the queen, or examine wounds that you’ve received on hard-to-see parts of your body.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Objects viewed through a spyglass are magnified to twice their size.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Standard iron spikes typically used with a hammer.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Essential for wizards, a spellbook is a leather-bound tome with 100 blank vellum pages suitable for recording spells.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A commodity used for bathing.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This two-handed, iron-headed hammer is good for smashing open treasure chests.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rope, has 2 hit points and can be burst with a DC 17 Strength check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Each signet ring has a distinctive design carved into it. When you press this ring into warm sealing wax, you leave an identifying mark.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A small whistle used for signaling.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard shovel used for digging.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When you press a signet ring into warm sealing wax, you leave an identifying mark.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sack can hold 1 cubic foot/ 30 pounds of gear.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rations consist of dry foods suitable for extended travel, including jerky, dried fruit, hardtack, and nuts.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A cloth or leather pouch can hold 1/5 cubic foot/ 6 pounds of gear - or up to 20 sling bullets or 50 blowgun needles, among other things.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can use a portable ram to break down doors. When doing so, you gain a +4 bonus on the Strength check. One other character can help you use the ram, giving you advantage on this check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can use the poison in this vial to coat one slashing or piercing weapon or up to three pieces of ammunition. Applying the poison takes an action. A creature hit by the poisoned weapon or ammunition must make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw or take 1d4 poison damage. Once applied, the poison retains potency for 1 minute before drying.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When a wall doesn’t offer handholds and footholds, you can make your own. A piton is a steel spike with an eye through which you can loop a rope.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A fragrant commodity typically used by the wealthy.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sheet of parchment is a piece of goat hide or sheepskin that has been prepared for writing on.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sheet of standard paper is made from cloth fibers.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can splash the oil in this flask or throw it up to 20 feet. Make a ranged attack, on a hit, the target is covered in oil. If the target takes fire damage before the oil dries (after 1 minute), an additional 5 fire damage is dealt. You can also pour a flask of oil on the ground to cover 5 feet of area. If lit, the oil burns for 2 rounds and deals 5 fire damage to any creature in the area.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A miner's pick is designed to concentrate the force of its blow on a small area.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This tin box contains a cup and simple cutlery. The box clamps together, and one side can be used as a cooking pan and the other as a plate or shallow bowl.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A scale includes a small balance, pans, and a suitable assortment of weights up to 2 pounds. With it, you can measure the exact weight of small objects, such as raw precious metals or trade goods, to help determine their worth.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: These metal restraints can bind a Small or Medium creature. Escaping the manacles requires a successful DC 20 Dexterity check. Breaking them requires a successful DC 20 Strength check. Each set of manacles comes with one key. Without the key, a creature proficient with thieves' tools can pick the manacles' lock with a successful DC 15 Dexterity check. Manacles have 15 hit points.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This lens allows a closer look at small objects. It is also useful as a substitute for flint and steel when starting fires. Lighting a fire with a magnifying glass requires light as bright as sunlight to focus, tinder to ignite, and about 5 minutes for the fire to ignite. A magnifying glass grants advantage on any ability check made to appraise or inspect an item that is small or highly detailed.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A key is provided with the lock. Without the key, a creature proficient with thieves' tools can pick this lock with a successful DC 15 Dexterity check. Your DM may decide that better locks are available for higher prices.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A lamp casts bright light in a 15-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This item is a straight, simple wooden ladder.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A jug or pitcher can hold 1 gallon of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: An iron pot can hold 1 gallon of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: An ink pen is a wooden stick with a special tip on the end. The tip draws ink in when dipped in a vial and leaves an ink trail when drawn across a surface.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Ink is typically used with an ink pen to write.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A creature that steps on the plate of this trap must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take 1d4 piercing damage and stop moving. Thereafter, until the creature breaks free of the trap, its movement is limited by the length of the chain. A creature can use its action to make a DC 13 Strength check. Each failed check deals 1 piercing damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard hourglass used to measure the passage of time.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A bullseye lantern casts bright light in a 60-foot cone and dim light for an additional 60 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A hooded lantern casts bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil. As an action, you can lower the hood, reducing the light to dim light in a 5-foot radius.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
You can splash the contents of this flask or throw it up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a target creature, treating the holy water as an improvised weapon. If the target is a fiend or undead, it takes 2d6 radiant damage.
Clerics and paladins can create holy water with a 1 hour ritual (also costs 25gp + 1 1st-level spell slot)

ContainedObjects.Description: This one-handed hammer with an iron head is useful for pounding pitons into a wall.

ContainedObjects.Description: When tied to the end of a rope, a grappling hook can secure the rope to a battlement, window ledge, tree limb, or other protrusion.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This kit includes a wooden rod, silken line, corkwood bobbers, steel hooks, lead sinkers, velvet lures, and narrow netting.

A druid can use a Yew Wand as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes is designed specifically to be expensive and to show it, including fancy, tailored clothes in whatever fashion happens to be the current style in the courts of the nobles. Precious metals and gems could be worked into the clothing.

ContainedObjects.Description: For 1 hour, a candle sheds bright light in a 5-foot radius and dim light for an additional 5 feet.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can spread a bag of caltrops to cover a square area that is 5 feet on a side. Any creature that enters the area must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or stop moving this turn and take 1 piercing damage. Taking this damage reduces the creature's walking speed by 10 feet until the creature regains at least 1 hit point. Moving through at half speed doesn't require a save.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard bell that rings, typically used for signaling.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You never know where you’re going to sleep, and a bedroll helps you get better sleep in a hayloft or on the cold ground. A bedroll consists of bedding and a blanket thin enough to be rolled up and tied. In an emergency, it can double as a stretcher.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A basket can hold 2 cubic feet/40 pounds of gear.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A barrel can hold 40 gallons of liquid, or 4 cubic feet of solid material.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can spill these tiny metal balls from their pouch to cover a level, square area that is 10 feet on a side. A creature moving across the covered area must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw or fall prone. A creature moving through the area at half speed doesn't need to make the save.

Proficiency with these tools lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to disarm traps or open locks.

ContainedObjects.Description: This small box contains a variety of papers and parchments, pens and inks, seals and sealing wax, gold and silver leaf, and other supplies necessary to create convincing forgeries of physical documents. Proficiency with this kit lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to create a physical forgery of a document.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This kit contains a variety of instruments such as clippers, mortar and pestle, and pouches and vials used by herbalists to create remedies and potions. Proficiency with this kit lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to identify or apply herbs. Also, proficiency with this kit is required to create antitoxin and any potion of healing.

In addition, these tools allow you to add your proficiency bonus to any ability check you make to avoid getting lost at sea.

You can also strap items, such as a bedroll or a coil of rope, to the outside of a backpack.

Each failed check deals 1 piercing damage.

Lighting a fire with a magnifying glass requires light as bright as sunlight to focus, tinder to ignite, and about 5 minutes for the fire to ignite. A magnifying glass grants advantage on any ability check made to appraise or inspect an item that is small or highly detailed.

ContainedObjects.Description: When tied to the end of a rope, a grappling hook can secure the rope to a battlement, window ledge, tree limb, or other protrusion.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token

Taking this damage reduces the creature's walking speed by 10 feet until the creature regains at least 1 hit point. Moving through at half speed doesn't require a save.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token

Also, proficiency with this kit is required to create antitoxin and any potion of healing.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: If you have proficiency with a given musical instrument, you can add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to play music with the instrument. A bard can use a musical instrument as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Description: These special tools include the items needed to pursue a craft or trade. Proficiency with a set of artisan's tools lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make using the tools in your craft. Each type of artisan's tools requires a separate proficiency.

ContainedObjects.Description: A bucket can hold 3 gallons of liquid, or 1/2 cubic foot of solid material.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A bottle can hold 1 1/2 pints of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A book might contain poetry, historical accounts, information pertaining to a particular field of lore, diagrams and notes on gnomish contraptions, or just about anything else that can be represented using text or pictures. A book of spells is a spellbook.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A set of pulleys with a cable threaded through them and a hook to attach to objects, a block and tackle allows you to hoist up to four times the weight you can normally lift.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A thick, quilted, blanket made to keep you warm in cold weather.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
A backpack is a leather pack carried on the back, typically with straps to secure it. A backpack can hold 1 cubic foot/ 30 pounds of gear.
You can also strap items, such as a bedroll or a coil of rope, to the outside of a backpack.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A creature that drinks this vial of liquid gains advantage on saving throws against poison for 1 hour. It confers no benefit to undead or constructs.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can throw this flask up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. Make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the alchemist's fire as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 1d4 fire damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature can end this damage by using its action to make a DC 10 Dexterity check to extinguish the flames.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can splash the contents of this vial onto a creature within 5 feet of you or throw the vial up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the acid as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 2d6 acid damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard tool used to make calculations.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes could consist of boots, a wool skirt or breeches, a sturdy belt, a shirt (perhaps with a vest or jacket), and an ample cloak with a hood.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard whetstone used to sharpen blades.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A waterskin can hold 4 pints of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A vial can hold 4 ounces of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A torch burns for 1 hour, providing bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. If you make a melee attack with a burning torch and hit, it deals 1 fire damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This small container holds flint, fire steel, and tinder (usually dry cloth soaked in light oil) used to kindle a fire. Using it to light a torch -- or anything else with abundant, exposed fuel -- takes an action. Lighting any other fire takes 1 minute.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A simple and portable canvas shelter, a tent sleeps two.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When you suspect a trap, you can put the end of your 10-foot pole through that hole in the wall instead of reaching in with your hand.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A steel mirror is handy when you want to look around corners, signal friends with reflected sunlight, keep an eye on a medusa, make sure that you look good enough to present yourself to the queen, or examine wounds that you’ve received on hard-to-see parts of your body.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Objects viewed through a spyglass are magnified to twice their size.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Standard iron spikes typically used with a hammer.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Essential for wizards, a spellbook is a leather-bound tome with 100 blank vellum pages suitable for recording spells.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A commodity used for bathing.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This two-handed, iron-headed hammer is good for smashing open treasure chests.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rope, has 2 hit points and can be burst with a DC 17 Strength check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Each signet ring has a distinctive design carved into it. When you press this ring into warm sealing wax, you leave an identifying mark.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A small whistle used for signaling.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard shovel used for digging.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When you press a signet ring into warm sealing wax, you leave an identifying mark.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sack can hold 1 cubic foot/ 30 pounds of gear.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rations consist of dry foods suitable for extended travel, including jerky, dried fruit, hardtack, and nuts.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A cloth or leather pouch can hold 1/5 cubic foot/ 6 pounds of gear - or up to 20 sling bullets or 50 blowgun needles, among other things.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
You regain hit points when you drink this potion.

Hit Points regained: 2d4+2

-DMG

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can use a portable ram to break down doors. When doing so, you gain a +4 bonus on the Strength check. One other character can help you use the ram, giving you advantage on this check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can use the poison in this vial to coat one slashing or piercing weapon or up to three pieces of ammunition. Applying the poison takes an action. A creature hit by the poisoned weapon or ammunition must make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw or take 1d4 poison damage. Once applied, the poison retains potency for 1 minute before drying.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When a wall doesn’t offer handholds and footholds, you can make your own. A piton is a steel spike with an eye through which you can loop a rope.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A fragrant commodity typically used by the wealthy.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sheet of parchment is a piece of goat hide or sheepskin that has been prepared for writing on.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sheet of standard paper is made from cloth fibers.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can splash the oil in this flask or throw it up to 20 feet. Make a ranged attack, on a hit, the target is covered in oil. If the target takes fire damage before the oil dries (after 1 minute), an additional 5 fire damage is dealt. You can also pour a flask of oil on the ground to cover 5 feet of area. If lit, the oil burns for 2 rounds and deals 5 fire damage to any creature in the area.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A miner's pick is designed to concentrate the force of its blow on a small area.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This tin box contains a cup and simple cutlery. The box clamps together, and one side can be used as a cooking pan and the other as a plate or shallow bowl.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A scale includes a small balance, pans, and a suitable assortment of weights up to 2 pounds. With it, you can measure the exact weight of small objects, such as raw precious metals or trade goods, to help determine their worth.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: These metal restraints can bind a Small or Medium creature. Escaping the manacles requires a successful DC 20 Dexterity check. Breaking them requires a successful DC 20 Strength check. Each set of manacles comes with one key. Without the key, a creature proficient with thieves' tools can pick the manacles' lock with a successful DC 15 Dexterity check. Manacles have 15 hit points.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This lens allows a closer look at small objects. It is also useful as a substitute for flint and steel when starting fires. Lighting a fire with a magnifying glass requires light as bright as sunlight to focus, tinder to ignite, and about 5 minutes for the fire to ignite. A magnifying glass grants advantage on any ability check made to appraise or inspect an item that is small or highly detailed.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A key is provided with the lock. Without the key, a creature proficient with thieves' tools can pick this lock with a successful DC 15 Dexterity check. Your DM may decide that better locks are available for higher prices.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A lamp casts bright light in a 15-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This item is a straight, simple wooden ladder.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A jug or pitcher can hold 1 gallon of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: An iron pot can hold 1 gallon of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: An ink pen is a wooden stick with a special tip on the end. The tip draws ink in when dipped in a vial and leaves an ink trail when drawn across a surface.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Ink is typically used with an ink pen to write.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A creature that steps on the plate of this trap must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take 1d4 piercing damage and stop moving. Thereafter, until the creature breaks free of the trap, its movement is limited by the length of the chain. A creature can use its action to make a DC 13 Strength check. Each failed check deals 1 piercing damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard hourglass used to measure the passage of time.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A bullseye lantern casts bright light in a 60-foot cone and dim light for an additional 60 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A hooded lantern casts bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil. As an action, you can lower the hood, reducing the light to dim light in a 5-foot radius.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
You can splash the contents of this flask or throw it up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a target creature, treating the holy water as an improvised weapon. If the target is a fiend or undead, it takes 2d6 radiant damage.
Clerics and paladins can create holy water with a 1 hour ritual (also costs 25gp + 1 1st-level spell slot)

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Holy Symbol

A holy symbol is a representation of a god or pantheon. A cleric or paladin can use a holy symbol as a spellcasting focus. To use the symbol in this way, the caster must hold it in hand, wear it visibly, or bear it on a shield.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Holy Symbol

A holy symbol is a representation of a god or pantheon. A cleric or paladin can use a holy symbol as a spellcasting focus. To use the symbol in this way, the caster must hold it in hand, wear it visibly, or bear it on a shield.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rope, has 2 hit points and can be burst with a DC 17 Strength check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This kit is a leather pouch containing bandages, salves, and splints. The kit has ten uses. As an action, you can expend one use of the kit to stabilize a creature that has 0 hit points, without needing to make a Wisdom (Medicine) check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This one-handed hammer with an iron head is useful for pounding pitons into a wall.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When tied to the end of a rope, a grappling hook can secure the rope to a battlement, window ledge, tree limb, or other protrusion.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A flask or tankard can hold 1 pint of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This kit includes a wooden rod, silken line, corkwood bobbers, steel hooks, lead sinkers, velvet lures, and narrow netting.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Druidic Focus

A druid can use a Yew Wand as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A quiver can hold up to 20 arrows.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Druidic Focus

A druid can use a Totem as a spellcasting focus

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Druidic Focus

A druid can use a Wooden Staff as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Druidic Focus

A druid can use a Sprig of Mistletoe (or holly) as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Using a crowbar grants advantage to Strength checks where the crowbar's leverage can be applied.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A component pouch is a small, watertight leather belt pouch that has compartments to hold all the material components and other special items you need to cast your spells, except for those components that have a specific cost (as indicated in a spell's description).

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Assuredly better than a drawing of one, contrary to some beliefs.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sum of money!

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard set of robes.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes is designed specifically to be expensive and to show it, including fancy, tailored clothes in whatever fashion happens to be the current style in the courts of the nobles. Precious metals and gems could be worked into the clothing.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes could consist of a loose shirt and baggy breeches, or a loose shirt and skirt or overdress. Cloth wrappings are used for shoes.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes is fashioned after a particular costume, typically meant for entertaining.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A climber's kit includes special pitons, boot tips, gloves, and a harness. You can use the climber's kit as an action to anchor yourself; when you do, you can't fall more than 25 feet from the point where you anchored yourself, and you can't climb more than 25 feet away from that point without undoing the anchor.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A chest can hold 12 cubic feet/ 300 pounds of gear.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A piece of chalk used for writing and marking on various surfaces.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A chain has 10 hit points. It can be burst with a successful DC 20 Strength check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This wooden case can hold up to 20 crossbow bolts.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This cylindrical leather case can hold up to ten rolled-up sheets of paper or five rolled-up sheets of parchment.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: For 1 hour, a candle sheds bright light in a 5-foot radius and dim light for an additional 5 feet.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can spread a bag of caltrops to cover a square area that is 5 feet on a side. Any creature that enters the area must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or stop moving this turn and take 1 piercing damage. Taking this damage reduces the creature's walking speed by 10 feet until the creature regains at least 1 hit point. Moving through at half speed doesn't require a save.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard bell that rings, typically used for signaling.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You never know where you’re going to sleep, and a bedroll helps you get better sleep in a hayloft or on the cold ground. A bedroll consists of bedding and a blanket thin enough to be rolled up and tied. In an emergency, it can double as a stretcher.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A basket can hold 2 cubic feet/40 pounds of gear.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A barrel can hold 40 gallons of liquid, or 4 cubic feet of solid material.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can spill these tiny metal balls from their pouch to cover a level, square area that is 10 feet on a side. A creature moving across the covered area must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw or fall prone. A creature moving through the area at half speed doesn't need to make the save.

ObjectStates.Description: A collection of official DnD treasures. If I add more content, it'll likely be to this bag.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Custom tokens used in various campaigns I've been a part of.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I wondered what it would be like to try to boop a kobold on its snout, but then I think a previous life reminded me that usually doesn't go well."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Melech found a flask that never seemed to run dry of water. It'll do in a pinch, but I would've preferred that he came across a never-empty flask of ale."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Skrit no like the first icon, must tell artist to draw him another one that doesn't make Skrit look silly."
-Skrit, Barbarian (and critic)

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I wouldn't call it particularly elegant to look at, but it's hard to argue with results."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I don't know where he got that frying pan from, but I have a feeling someone somewhere in the world is short one pan in their kitchen."
-Garlen Sunbourne, Paladin

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"I didn't STEAL it from him, I took it off his person after DISARMING him. That's a key difference, I'll have you know."
-Garlen Sunbourne, Paladin

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"How poetic. I wanted to forsake the darkness, and yet here it offers me strength."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"The light of Pelor illuminates my path!"
-Garlen Sunbourne, Paladin

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Found amongst a pile of treasures, used by none since there was a better sword in the pile as well."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Gift from king! NO TAKE."
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Skrit sees light!... it's alright."
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"At first, I questioned the sanity of the monk as he waded into the fray of battle without even so much as a scrap of armor on him. However, I changed my mind when there was not a single scratch on him after the fight. He moved like the very breeze itself, dodging any attack that came his way.
Maybe he could only be pinned down if you offered him his favourite ale."
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"You know, I don't think I ever discerned what this does, but I think the paladin was envious of it, so it gave me some satisfaction at the very least"
-Melech Lothran, Warlock

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"Grabby grabby for the shinies, slashy slashy for the ones who take shinies!"
-Skrit, Barbarian

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"The ancient one of the lizardmen gave us these as thanks for freeing his followers from the parasitic creatures of the forest. Keeping it close to me makes me feel stronger. Either that or I got a good rest last night."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"A mystical set of beads that grant wishes. Anything I could ever want, yet I feel I already have enough.
Wonder if I could make a proverb out of that."
-Frederick Steelfist, Monk

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
"SSSSSKRRRRRRRIIIIIIITTTTT!!!!!!"
-Skrit, Barbarian

This item has not been identified yet.
Use at your own risk.

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: A collection of commonplace items, as well as various ammunition and artisan's tools.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A bucket can hold 3 gallons of liquid, or 1/2 cubic foot of solid material.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A bottle can hold 1 1/2 pints of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A book might contain poetry, historical accounts, information pertaining to a particular field of lore, diagrams and notes on gnomish contraptions, or just about anything else that can be represented using text or pictures. A book of spells is a spellbook.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A set of pulleys with a cable threaded through them and a hook to attach to objects, a block and tackle allows you to hoist up to four times the weight you can normally lift.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A thick, quilted, blanket made to keep you warm in cold weather.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
A backpack is a leather pack carried on the back, typically with straps to secure it. A backpack can hold 1 cubic foot/ 30 pounds of gear.
You can also strap items, such as a bedroll or a coil of rope, to the outside of a backpack.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A creature that drinks this vial of liquid gains advantage on saving throws against poison for 1 hour. It confers no benefit to undead or constructs.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can throw this flask up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. Make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the alchemist's fire as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 1d4 fire damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature can end this damage by using its action to make a DC 10 Dexterity check to extinguish the flames.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can splash the contents of this vial onto a creature within 5 feet of you or throw the vial up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the acid as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 2d6 acid damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard tool used to make calculations.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Arcane Focus

An arcane focus is a special item designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This set of clothes could consist of boots, a wool skirt or breeches, a sturdy belt, a shirt (perhaps with a vest or jacket), and an ample cloak with a hood.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard whetstone used to sharpen blades.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A waterskin can hold 4 pints of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A vial can hold 4 ounces of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A torch burns for 1 hour, providing bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. If you make a melee attack with a burning torch and hit, it deals 1 fire damage.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This small container holds flint, fire steel, and tinder (usually dry cloth soaked in light oil) used to kindle a fire. Using it to light a torch -- or anything else with abundant, exposed fuel -- takes an action. Lighting any other fire takes 1 minute.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A simple and portable canvas shelter, a tent sleeps two.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When you suspect a trap, you can put the end of your 10-foot pole through that hole in the wall instead of reaching in with your hand.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A steel mirror is handy when you want to look around corners, signal friends with reflected sunlight, keep an eye on a medusa, make sure that you look good enough to present yourself to the queen, or examine wounds that you’ve received on hard-to-see parts of your body.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Objects viewed through a spyglass are magnified to twice their size.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Standard iron spikes typically used with a hammer.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Essential for wizards, a spellbook is a leather-bound tome with 100 blank vellum pages suitable for recording spells.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A commodity used for bathing.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This two-handed, iron-headed hammer is good for smashing open treasure chests.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rope, has 2 hit points and can be burst with a DC 17 Strength check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Each signet ring has a distinctive design carved into it. When you press this ring into warm sealing wax, you leave an identifying mark.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A small whistle used for signaling.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard shovel used for digging.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When you press a signet ring into warm sealing wax, you leave an identifying mark.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sack can hold 1 cubic foot/ 30 pounds of gear.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Rations consist of dry foods suitable for extended travel, including jerky, dried fruit, hardtack, and nuts.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A cloth or leather pouch can hold 1/5 cubic foot/ 6 pounds of gear - or up to 20 sling bullets or 50 blowgun needles, among other things.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
You regain hit points when you drink this potion.

Hit Points regained: 2d4+2

-DMG

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can use a portable ram to break down doors. When doing so, you gain a +4 bonus on the Strength check. One other character can help you use the ram, giving you advantage on this check.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can use the poison in this vial to coat one slashing or piercing weapon or up to three pieces of ammunition. Applying the poison takes an action. A creature hit by the poisoned weapon or ammunition must make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw or take 1d4 poison damage. Once applied, the poison retains potency for 1 minute before drying.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: When a wall doesn’t offer handholds and footholds, you can make your own. A piton is a steel spike with an eye through which you can loop a rope.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A fragrant commodity typically used by the wealthy.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sheet of parchment is a piece of goat hide or sheepskin that has been prepared for writing on.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A sheet of standard paper is made from cloth fibers.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can splash the oil in this flask or throw it up to 20 feet. Make a ranged attack, on a hit, the target is covered in oil. If the target takes fire damage before the oil dries (after 1 minute), an additional 5 fire damage is dealt. You can also pour a flask of oil on the ground to cover 5 feet of area. If lit, the oil burns for 2 rounds and deals 5 fire damage to any creature in the area.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A miner's pick is designed to concentrate the force of its blow on a small area.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This tin box contains a cup and simple cutlery. The box clamps together, and one side can be used as a cooking pan and the other as a plate or shallow bowl.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A scale includes a small balance, pans, and a suitable assortment of weights up to 2 pounds. With it, you can measure the exact weight of small objects, such as raw precious metals or trade goods, to help determine their worth.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: These metal restraints can bind a Small or Medium creature. Escaping the manacles requires a successful DC 20 Dexterity check. Breaking them requires a successful DC 20 Strength check. Each set of manacles comes with one key. Without the key, a creature proficient with thieves' tools can pick the manacles' lock with a successful DC 15 Dexterity check. Manacles have 15 hit points.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This lens allows a closer look at small objects. It is also useful as a substitute for flint and steel when starting fires. Lighting a fire with a magnifying glass requires light as bright as sunlight to focus, tinder to ignite, and about 5 minutes for the fire to ignite. A magnifying glass grants advantage on any ability check made to appraise or inspect an item that is small or highly detailed.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A key is provided with the lock. Without the key, a creature proficient with thieves' tools can pick this lock with a successful DC 15 Dexterity check. Your DM may decide that better locks are available for higher prices.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A lamp casts bright light in a 15-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. Once lit, it burns for 6 hours on a flask (1 pint) of oil.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: This item is a straight, simple wooden ladder.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A jug or pitcher can hold 1 gallon of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: An iron pot can hold 1 gallon of liquid.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: An ink pen is a wooden stick with a special tip on the end. The tip draws ink in when dipped in a vial and leaves an ink trail when drawn across a surface.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Ink is typically used with an ink pen to write.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A creature that steps on the plate of this trap must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take 1d4 piercing damage and stop moving. Thereafter, until the creature breaks free of the trap, its movement is limited by the length of the chain. A creature can use its action to make a DC 13 Strength check. Each failed check deals 1 piercing damage.

You can splash the contents of this flask or throw it up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a target creature, treating the holy water as an improvised weapon. If the target is a fiend or undead, it takes 2d6 radiant damage.
Clerics and paladins can create holy water with a 1 hour ritual (also costs 25gp + 1 1st-level spell slot)

You can use the climber's kit as an action to anchor yourself; when you do, you can't fall more than 25 feet from the point where you anchored yourself, and you can't climb more than 25 feet away from that point without undoing the anchor.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can spread a bag of caltrops to cover a square area that is 5 feet on a side. Any creature that enters the area must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or stop moving this turn and take 1 piercing damage. Taking this damage reduces the creature's walking speed by 10 feet until the creature regains at least 1 hit point. Moving through at half speed doesn't require a save.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: A standard bell that rings, typically used for signaling.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You never know where you’re going to sleep, and a bedroll helps you get better sleep in a hayloft or on the cold ground. A bedroll consists of bedding and a blanket thin enough to be rolled up and tied. In an emergency, it can double as a stretcher.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: As an action, you can spill these tiny metal balls from their pouch to cover a level, square area that is 10 feet on a side. A creature moving across the covered area must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw or fall prone. A creature moving through the area at half speed doesn't need to make the save.
